# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Spring Boot + DynamoDB with CloudMock for local development.

## Getting Started

### 1. Start CloudMock

```bash
docker compose up
# or
npx cloudmock
```

### 2. Run the application

```bash
mvn spring-boot:run
```

API available at http://localhost:8080.

## API

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | /items | Create an item |
| GET | /items | List all items |
| GET | /items/{id} | Get an item |
| DELETE | /items/{id} | Delete an item |

Example:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/items \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"id":"1","name":"Widget"}'

curl http://localhost:8080/items/1
```

## Testing

```bash
mvn test
```

Tests use `CloudMock.start()` — no Docker required.

## CloudMock DevTools

Open [http://localhost:4500](http://localhost:4500) for traces and DynamoDB metrics.
